title: Psycho Killer | Official Trailer
description:
Enter the Mind of a Psycho Killer.

PSYCHO KILLER. Only in theaters February 20, 2026


From 20th Century Studios and the producers of ‚ÄúBarbarian‚Äù and ‚ÄúWeapons‚Äù comes ‚ÄúPsycho Killer,‚Äù a terrifying cross-country road trip starring Georgina Campbell and James Preston Rogers, directed by Gavin Polone, which opens in theaters February 20, 2026. 
 
Following the brutal murder of her husband, a Kansas highway patrol officer (Georgina Campbell) sets out on a journey to track down the perpetrator. As the hunt progresses, she comes to realize the man responsible (James Preston Rogers) is a sadistic serial killer, and the depth of his mental depravity and his sinister agenda is more twisted than anyone could have imagined. The film, which also stars Grace Dove, Logan Miller, and Malcolm McDowell, is written by Andrew Kevin Walker and produced by Roy Lee, Matt Berenson, Andrew Kevin Walker, and Arnon Milchan, with Martin Moszkowicz, Robert Kulzer, Yariv Milchan, Natalie Lehmann, and Kat Landsberg serving as executive producers.

title: Black Phone 2 | Get Tickets Now
description:
Discover the secret behind the mask. Black Phone 2 only in theaters October 17. Get tickets now. 

---
Four years ago, 13-year-old Finn killed his abductor and escaped, becoming the sole survivor of The Grabber. But true evil transcends death ‚Ä¶ and the phone is ringing again. 

Four-time Academy Award¬Æ nominee Ethan Hawke returns to the most sinister role of his career as The Grabber seeks vengeance on Finn (Mason Thames) from beyond the grave by menacing Finn‚Äôs younger sister, Gwen (Madeleine McGraw). 

As Finn, now 17, struggles with life after his captivity, the headstrong 15-year-old Gwen begins receiving calls in her dreams from the black phone and seeing disturbing visions of three boys being stalked at a winter camp known as Alpine Lake. 

Determined to solve the mystery and end the torment for both her and her brother, Gwen persuades Finn to visit the camp during a winter storm. There, she uncovers a shattering intersection between The Grabber and her own family‚Äôs history. Together, she and Finn must confront a killer who has grown more powerful in death and more significant to them than either could imagine.

From returning visionary writer-director Scott Derrickson, Black Phone 2 is written again by Derrickson & C. Robert Cargill, based on characters created by Joe Hill. The film is produced by Jason Blum, Derrickson and Cargill. The executive producers are Adam Hendricks and Ryan Turek.

The cast includes Oscar¬Æ nominee Demi√°n Bichir (The Nun, A Better Life) as the supervisor of the camp, Arianna Rivas (A Working Man) as his niece, Miguel Mora (The Black Phone) as the brother of one of The Grabber‚Äôs victims, and Jeremy Davies, returning as Finn and Gwen‚Äôs father, Terrence. Other new cast members include Maev Beaty (Beau is Afraid) and Graham Abbey (Under the Banner of Heaven). 

Universal Pictures and Blumhouse‚Äôs horror phenomenon The Black Phone, released in 2022, received widespread critical acclaim and earned more than $160 million.

title: The Carpenter's Son - Official Trailer | Nicolas Cage, Noah Jupe, FKA twigs | In Theaters Nov 14
description:
In theaters November 14. 
http://thecarpenterssonmovie.com/ 

A remote village in Roman-era Egypt explodes into spiritual warfare when a carpenter, his wife and their child are targeted by supernatural forces in The Carpenter‚Äôs Son. Joseph (Nicolas Cage), Mary (FKA twigs) and their teenage son Jesus (Noah Jupe) have lived for years under threat, clinging to their faith and traditions. But a stopover in a small settlement unleashes growing chaos when a mysterious stranger (Isla Johnston) tries to entice young Jesus to abandon his devout father‚Äôs rules. With every pull of temptation, the boy is lured into a forbidden world, as a terrified Joseph realizes that a demonic power is at work. Violent, unnatural events inexplicably follow Jesus, and he begins to experience nightmarish visions of the future. Finally, he learns the fearsome truth about his new playmate, as well as the child‚Äôs real name: Satan. Writer and director Lotfy Nathan, drawing from his Coptic Christian background, delivers a meticulously crafted, genre-bending supernatural thriller packed with unshakeable images of the divine and demonic at war. 

Starring Nicolas Cage, Noah Jupe, Isla Johnston and FKA twigs

title: Creedence Clearwater Revival - Have You Ever Seen The Rain (Official Spanish Lyric Video)
description:
The official Spanish lyric video of ‚ÄúHave You Ever Seen The Rain‚Äù taken from Creedence Clearwater Revival‚Äôs greatest hits collection, Chronicle.

About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival‚Äôs 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom‚ÄØFogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of‚ÄØthe day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ 

During their short time together as a band (1968 ‚Äì 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity. They‚Äôve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits, six Platinum albums (two of which went to number one) and one Gold album. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.‚ÄØ 

Creedence Clearwater Revival‚Äôs canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Songs like ‚ÄúBad Moon Rising,‚Äù ‚ÄúDown on the Corner,‚Äù ‚ÄúFortunate Son,‚Äù ‚ÄúHave You Ever Seen the Rain,‚Äù ‚ÄúProud Mary,‚Äù ‚ÄúBorn on the Bayou,‚Äù ‚ÄúTravelin‚Äô Band‚Äù and ‚ÄúUp Around the Bend‚Äù have been ingrained into pop culture ‚Äî not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.‚ÄØ‚ÄØ 

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves and television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America‚Äôs greatest rock ‚Äôn‚Äô roll band.

title: We Played Every Slot In The Casino!
description:
We are BACK at the Casino, playing EVERY LAST SLOT in the High-Limit room at Jamul! This is a huge task, so we called in the help of Rack'em Stack'em Robby himself @PlaySpinQuest ,  my sister and her husband @omfg_slots , and a NEWBIE @Tayolarson ! We better get AT LEAST 50 hand-pays on this video... Thank you all for watching! You‚Äôre all beautiful, and I truly appreciate every single one of you for riding along on this crazy journey.  Wish me luck, and I‚Äôll see you in the next one! Let‚Äôs go to war.

Brettski adjusted his mirrored shades as the high-limit room doors swung open, revealing a glittering jungle of chrome, LED lights, and the hypnotic chimes of high-stakes hope. Behind him trailed Rack‚Äôem Stack‚Äôem Robby, a walking legend with a diamond-encrusted money clip, Kayla and Chris‚ÄîYouTube royalty from omfg_slots‚Äîand Mateo, whose only claim to fame was surviving three Vegas trips without remembering how he got back.

They brought $50,000 and one rule: play every single machine in the room. No skips. No mercy.

Robby slapped five grand into a dragon-themed slot. First spin‚Äîjackpot. The machine lit up like New Year‚Äôs Eve in Macau. Chris caught it all on camera, screaming ‚ÄúTHIS IS UNREAL!‚Äù while Kayla swirled champagne like a boss.

Machine after machine fell. Triple diamonds, buffaloes, ancient Aztec gods‚Äîthey couldn‚Äôt miss. Mateo somehow hit a $15,000 win on a machine he thought was broken. Brettski was riding the wave, heart pounding. This wasn‚Äôt gambling. This was destiny.

Then came it‚Äîa machine in the corner, older than the others. No lights. No sounds. Just a flickering CRT screen that read: ‚ÄúDare to Bet?‚Äù

Robby raised an eyebrow. ‚ÄúLooks rigged.‚Äù

Brettski smirked. ‚ÄúPerfect.‚Äù

He slid in a $500 bill. The screen went black. A low mechanical hum filled the air.

Then a voice‚Äîdeep, metallic, almost human‚Äîwhispered:
‚ÄúYou‚Äôve been chosen.‚Äù

The reels spun violently, symbols nobody recognized‚Äîstrange runes, a clock melting, a skull with ruby eyes.

The machine stopped.

Nothing.

All their phones went black.

The casino lights flickered.

Kayla whispered, ‚ÄúWhat the heck did you do?‚Äù

From behind the cashier‚Äôs cage, a door creaked open‚Äîone none of them had noticed before. Smoke poured out, along with something‚Ä¶ else.

Brettski looked at Robby.

‚ÄúWanna double down?‚Äù

To be continued. üé∞üíÄ

ABOUT CHELSEA FOOTBALL CLUB 

Founded in 1905, Chelsea Football Club is an English professional football club based in Fulham, West London with Stamford Bridge as the home of the club. Competing in the Premier League - the top division of English football, the club has had many successes, winning five Premier League titles. The club won their first major honour, the League championship in 1955, followed by the FA Cup in 1970, their first European honour, the Cup Winners' Cup in 1971, and became the third English club to win the Club World Cup in 2022. 

As the Pride of London, Chelsea FC is one of the most successful clubs in terms of overall trophies won. They are the only club to have won all three major European competitions twice and, following their 2025 UEFA Europa Conference League triumph, they have now completed victories in all five major UEFA club tournaments. Domestically, they have claimed six league titles, eight FA Cups, five League Cups, and four FA Community Shields. Internationally, Chelsea have lifted the UEFA Champions League, UEFA Europa League, UEFA Cup Winners‚Äô Cup, UEFA Super Cup, FIFA Club World Cup, and now the UEFA Conference League, winning each of the first five twice since their inception.

Creedence Clearwater Revival‚Äôs 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom‚ÄØFogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of‚ÄØthe day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ 

During their short time together as a band (1968 ‚Äì 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity. They‚Äôve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits, six Platinum albums (two of which went to number one) and one Gold album. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.‚ÄØ 

Creedence Clearwater Revival‚Äôs canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Songs like ‚ÄúBad Moon Rising,‚Äù ‚ÄúDown on the Corner,‚Äù ‚ÄúFortunate Son,‚Äù ‚ÄúHave You Ever Seen the Rain,‚Äù ‚ÄúProud Mary,‚Äù ‚ÄúBorn on the Bayou,‚Äù ‚ÄúTravelin‚Äô Band‚Äù and ‚ÄúUp Around the Bend‚Äù have been ingrained into pop culture ‚Äî not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.‚ÄØ‚ÄØ

title: Official Trailer | Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya | Nirvair Pannu | Tanu Grewal 10 Oct | Jass Records
description:
Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya

Set in Punjab during the 1990s, Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya is a soulful tale that bridges love, poetry, and history across borders. Nirvair Pannu (Sooba), a young man running a telephone shop near the Indo-Pak border, finds solace in the verses aired on Lahore Radio. Unknown to him, those poignant words belong to Naazo, a mute girl in Pakistan who expresses her voice through poetry while struggling with her family‚Äôs hardships. 
A twist of fate connects them when army wireless sets fall into their hands, creating a secret channel across the border. Amid deception, smuggling, and family struggles, Nirvair discovers that the mysterious poetess he has long admired is Naazo herself.
What follows is an emotional journey that not only unites two hearts but also revives the unfinished stories of Partition‚Äîwhere love, loss, and courage once redefined destinies.
